│   ├── Vision.md
│   ├── Architecture.md
│   └── TODO.md
├── Plugins/
├── Source/
└── .gitignore
```

---

## 🛠️ Technical Directions

### Core Game Systems

- FPS Controller (use base UE5, customize later)
- Interactive Objects system via Blueprint Interfaces
- Central `GameEventManager` (BP or C++ or hybrid)
- Modular Gameplay Actor Components (e.g., Interact, Highlight, Animate)

### UI/UX

- Minimal, smooth and modern style
- Use widget components or world-space UI
- Include optional “narrative” bits: floating thoughts, hints, etc.

### Shader Goals

- Emissive decals
- World-space UV effects
- Minimalist post-process shaders
- Outlines or screen space effects for visual feedback

---

## 🧰 Third Party & Tools

- Mixamo (characters + simple idle/walk animations)
- Quixel Megascans (free assets from Epic Games)
- VSCode for:

  - Source control
  - Markdown docs

- Possibly: Asset Manager plugins or Shader tools from Marketplace (safe license only)

---

## 📌 Steam Release Notes

- Learn and document process to:

  - Package for Windows
  - Prepare a store page
  - Ensure assets are license-compliant
  - Handle game settings, input configs, README, and disclaimers

---

## ✅ Success Criteria

- A playable, visually impressive, lightweight FPS demo
- Solid code architecture that reflects your philosophy
- Everything documented, with clear dev logs and commits
- Uploaded for free on Steam, itch.io or similar
- People finish the game and say: "That was actually fun. Who made this?"

---

**Let’s go Omar. One module at a time. One system at a time. By December 2025 — you’ll have built something timeless.**
